<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-43-0572 </DOCNO><TEXT>A rock bolt used for securing lagging or lagging reinforcements in miningand tunnel construction, comprises a bolt fixed by means of adhesivein a drill hole and projecting from the drill hole for engagement bya convex anchor plate for clamping the lagging, and by a base plate engagedby a nut and fixed to a yieldable stirrup member which engages a washer,the base plate being rectangular so that it can pass through a rectangularopening in the convex anchor plate for rotation through 90 degrees intoholding engagement. Increased tension in the bolt due to rock movementis accommodated by yielding of the stirrup member.</TEXT></DOC>